dsMIB.name: dsMIB

revisions.description: This revision of this MIB is published in RFC 2605. This revision obsoletes RFC 1567. It is incompatible with the original MIB and so it has been renamed from dsaMIB to dsMIB.
The original version of this MIB was published in RFC 1567.

dsMIB.organization: IETF Mail and Directory Management Working Group
dsMIB.contactinfo: Glenn Mansfield Postal: Cyber Solutions Inc. 6-6-3, Minami Yoshinari Aoba-ku, Sendai, Japan 989-3204. Tel: +81-22-303-4012 Fax: +81-22-303-4015 E-mail: glenn@cysols.com Working Group E-mail: ietf-madman@innosoft.com To subscribe: ietf-madman-request@innosoft.com
dsMIB.description: The MIB module for monitoring Directory Services.

dsTable.name: dsTable
dsTable.description: The table holding information related to the Directory Servers.

dsTableEntry.name: dsTableEntry
dsTableEntry.description: Entry containing summary description for a Directory Server.

dsServerType.name: dsServerType
dsServerType.description: This object indicates whether the server is a frontend or, a backend or, both. If the server is a frontend, then the frontEndDirectoryServer bit will be set. Similarly for the backend.

dsServerDescription.name: dsServerDescription
dsServerDescription.description: A text description of the application. This information is intended to identify and briefly describe the application in a status display.

dsMasterEntries.name: dsMasterEntries
dsMasterEntries.description: Number of entries mastered in the Directory Server.

dsCopyEntries.name: dsCopyEntries
dsCopyEntries.description: Number of entries for which systematic (slave) copies are maintained in the Directory Server.

dsCacheEntries.name: dsCacheEntries
dsCacheEntries.description: Number of entries cached (non-systematic copies) in the Directory Server. This will include the entries that are cached partially. The negative cache is not counted.

dsCacheHits.name: dsCacheHits
dsCacheHits.description: Number of operations that were serviced from the locally held cache.

dsSlaveHits.name: dsSlaveHits
dsSlaveHits.description: Number of operations that were serviced from the locally held object replications ( copy- entries).

dsApplIfOpsTable.name: dsApplIfOpsTable
dsApplIfOpsTable.description: The table holding information related to the Directory Server operations.

dsApplIfOpsEntry.name: dsApplIfOpsEntry
dsApplIfOpsEntry.description: Entry containing operations related statistics for a Directory Server.

dsApplIfProtocolIndex.name: dsApplIfProtocolIndex
dsApplIfProtocolIndex.description: An index to uniquely identify an entry corresponding to a application-layer protocol interface. This index is used for lexicographic ordering of the table.

dsApplIfProtocol.name: dsApplIfProtocol
dsApplIfProtocol.description: An identification of the protocol being used by the application on this interface. For an OSI Application, this will be the Application Context. For Internet applications, the IANA maintains a registry[22] of the OIDs which correspond to well-known applications. If the application protocol is not listed in the registry, an OID value of the form {applTCPProtoID port} or {applUDProtoID port} are used for TCP-based and UDP-based protocols, respectively. In either case 'port' corresponds to the primary port number being used by the protocol. The OIDs applTCPProtoID and applUDPProtoID are defined in NETWORK-SERVICES-MIB

dsApplIfUnauthBinds.name: dsApplIfUnauthBinds
dsApplIfUnauthBinds.description: Number of unauthenticated/anonymous bind requests received.

dsApplIfSimpleAuthBinds.name: dsApplIfSimpleAuthBinds
dsApplIfSimpleAuthBinds.description: Number of bind requests that were authenticated using simple authentication procedures like password checks. This includes the password authentication using SASL mechanisms like CRAM-MD5.

dsApplIfStrongAuthBinds.name: dsApplIfStrongAuthBinds
dsApplIfStrongAuthBinds.description: Number of bind requests that were authenticated using TLS and X.500 strong authentication procedures. This includes the binds that were authenticated using external authentication procedures.

dsApplIfBindSecurityErrors.name: dsApplIfBindSecurityErrors
dsApplIfBindSecurityErrors.description: Number of bind requests that have been rejected due to inappropriate authentication or invalid credentials.

dsApplIfInOps.name: dsApplIfInOps
dsApplIfInOps.description: Number of requests received from DUAs or other Directory Servers.

dsApplIfSearchOps.name: dsApplIfSearchOps
dsApplIfSearchOps.description: Number of search requests- baseObject searches, oneLevel searches and whole subtree searches, received.

dsApplIfOneLevelSearchOps.name: dsApplIfOneLevelSearchOps
dsApplIfOneLevelSearchOps.description: Number of oneLevel search requests received.

dsApplIfWholeSubtreeSearchOps.name: dsApplIfWholeSubtreeSearchOps
dsApplIfWholeSubtreeSearchOps.description: Number of whole subtree search requests received.

dsApplIfReferrals.name: dsApplIfReferrals
dsApplIfReferrals.description: Number of referrals returned in response to requests for operations.

dsApplIfChainings.name: dsApplIfChainings
dsApplIfChainings.description: Number of operations forwarded by this Directory Server to other Directory Servers.

dsApplIfSecurityErrors.name: dsApplIfSecurityErrors
dsApplIfSecurityErrors.description: Number of requests received which did not meet the security requirements.

dsApplIfErrors.name: dsApplIfErrors
dsApplIfErrors.description: Number of requests that could not be serviced due to errors other than security errors, and referrals. A partially serviced operation will not be counted as an error. The errors include naming-related, update-related, attribute-related and service-related errors.

dsApplIfReplicationUpdatesIn.name: dsApplIfReplicationUpdatesIn
dsApplIfReplicationUpdatesIn.description: Number of replication updates fetched or received from supplier Directory Servers.

dsApplIfReplicationUpdatesOut.name: dsApplIfReplicationUpdatesOut
dsApplIfReplicationUpdatesOut.description: Number of replication updates sent to or taken by consumer Directory Servers.

dsApplIfInBytes.name: dsApplIfInBytes
dsApplIfInBytes.description: Incoming traffic, in bytes, on the interface. This will include requests from DUAs as well as responses from other Directory Servers.

dsApplIfOutBytes.name: dsApplIfOutBytes
dsApplIfOutBytes.description: Outgoing traffic in bytes on the interface. This will include responses to DUAs and Directory Servers as well as requests to other Directory Servers.

dsIntTable.name: dsIntTable
dsIntTable.description: Each row of this table contains some details related to the history of the interaction of the monitored Directory Server with its peer Directory Servers.

dsIntEntry.name: dsIntEntry
dsIntEntry.description: Entry containing interaction details of a Directory Server with a peer Directory Server.

dsIntEntIndex.name: dsIntEntIndex
dsIntEntIndex.description: Together with applIndex and dsApplIfProtocolIndex, this object forms the unique key to identify the conceptual row which contains useful info on the (attempted) interaction between the Directory Server (referred to by applIndex) and a peer Directory Server using a particular protocol.

dsIntEntDirectoryName.name: dsIntEntDirectoryName
dsIntEntDirectoryName.description: Distinguished Name of the peer Directory Server to which this entry pertains.

dsIntEntTimeOfCreation.name: dsIntEntTimeOfCreation
dsIntEntTimeOfCreation.description: The value of sysUpTime when this row was created. If the entry was created before the network management subsystem was initialized, this object will contain a value of zero.

dsIntEntTimeOfLastAttempt.name: dsIntEntTimeOfLastAttempt
dsIntEntTimeOfLastAttempt.description: The value of sysUpTime when the last attempt was made to contact the peer Directory Server. If the last attempt was made before the network management subsystem was initialized, this object will contain a value of zero.

dsIntEntTimeOfLastSuccess.name: dsIntEntTimeOfLastSuccess
dsIntEntTimeOfLastSuccess.description: The value of sysUpTime when the last attempt made to contact the peer Directory Server was successful. If there have been no successful attempts this entry will have a value of zero. If the last successful attempt was made before the network management subsystem was initialized, this object will contain a value of zero.

dsIntEntFailuresSinceLastSuccess.name: dsIntEntFailuresSinceLastSuccess
dsIntEntFailuresSinceLastSuccess.description: The number of failures since the last time an attempt to contact the peer Directory Server was successful. If there have been no successful attempts, this counter will contain the number of failures since this entry was created.

dsIntEntFailures.name: dsIntEntFailures
dsIntEntFailures.description: Cumulative failures in contacting the peer Directory Server since the creation of this entry.

dsIntEntSuccesses.name: dsIntEntSuccesses
dsIntEntSuccesses.description: Cumulative successes in contacting the peer Directory Server since the creation of this entry.

dsIntEntURL.name: dsIntEntURL
dsIntEntURL.description: URL of the peer Directory Server.

dsEntryCompliance.name: dsEntryCompliance
dsEntryCompliance.description: The compliance statement for SNMP entities which implement the DIRECTORY-SERVER-MIB for a summary overview of the Directory Servers .

dsOpsCompliance.name: dsOpsCompliance
dsOpsCompliance.description: The compliance statement for SNMP entities which implement the DIRECTORY-SERVER-MIB for monitoring Directory Server operations, entry statistics and cache performance.

dsIntCompliance.name: dsIntCompliance
dsIntCompliance.description: The compliance statement for SNMP entities which implement the DIRECTORY-SERVER-MIB for monitoring Directory Server operations and the interaction of the Directory Server with peer Directory Servers.

dsOpsIntCompliance.name: dsOpsIntCompliance
dsOpsIntCompliance.description: The compliance statement for SNMP entities which implement the DIRECTORY-SERVER-MIB for monitoring Directory Server operations and the interaction of the Directory Server with peer Directory Servers.

dsEntryGroup.name: dsEntryGroup
dsEntryGroup.description: A collection of objects for a summary overview of the Directory Servers.

dsOpsGroup.name: dsOpsGroup
dsOpsGroup.description: A collection of objects for monitoring the Directory Server operations.

dsIntGroup.name: dsIntGroup
dsIntGroup.description: A collection of objects for monitoring the Directory Server's interaction with peer Directory Servers.
